                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/118.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed Obregon has issued decree exacting payment by 6 p.m. Friday
                    next, ¾ of 1 per cent on capital corporations and private individuals in federal
                    district including foreigners, penalties for nonpayment being confiscation,
                    appointment of receivers and imprisonment for 30 days.</p>
                <p>Request Carranza order reconsideration this decree as affecting American citizens
                    and other foreigners. Point out injustice of short time limit and unwarrantedly
                    drastic penalties. Request immediate action. Report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
